<seg id=1> China Continues to Carring on the Open Financial Policy to the Outside World. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency. Beijing. Jan. 16. (Reporters  Xu Xingtang and Qian Yuhong) Dai Xianglong, President of the People's Bank of China, said China is going on to carry out the open financial policy. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> Todsay, Dai Xianglong stressed at the news press held for journalists at home and abroad that China will not give up the open financial policy because of the financial crisis in some Southeast Asian countries. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> He said, last year some more foreign banks and insurance companies set up their branches in China. By the end of this year, over 170 business financial organizations will have been set up in China by foreign capital. </seg>
<seg id=5> In the future, foreign banks and insurance companies are allowed to adequately increase their branches in China, and meanwhile to enlarge foreign banks' tentative businesses to deal with RMB services. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> He also stressed that in the future the conditions for foreign financial organizations to apply for business service in China, the qualifications of the senior staff and the legality of their businesses will be managed with greater caution. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> He said, because there is no timetable in the convertability under RMB capital account, there exists no question to extend this process because of the Southeast Asian financial crisis. </seg>
<seg id=8> However, in the aspect of opening the capital account, we are to take lessons from the Southeast Asian financial crisis, and to take a more cautious attitude. </seg>
</p>
